)+1.\n\nSo individually minimum is ceil(a_i/3). But jointly we need a shared pool.\n\nThe number of 3-coins needed: max over all a_i of floor(a_i/3). Similarly for 2s and 1s but they can share.\n\nActually c3 = max(floor(a_i/3)), but then for a_i with remainder 1, we need a 1-coin, and for remainder 2, a 2-coin. c1 = 1 if any a_i % 3 == 1, c2 = 1 if any a_i % 3 == 2. But also if a_i%3==1 and c2>=1, we can use one 2 and reduce 3s... but c3 is already max.\n\nLet me try: answer = max(ceil(a_i/3)) for each a_i, plus adjustments for remainders.\n\nT = int(input())\nfor _ in range(T):\n    n = int(input())\n    a = list(map(int, input().split()))\n    c3 = max(x // 3 for x in a)\n    need1 = any(x % 3 == 1 for x in a)\n    need2 = any(x % 3 == 2 for x in a)\n    print(c3 + need1 + need2)",
